From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Project OS Build Fix <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sat, 31 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] libcpu: fix const qualifier in riscv_disasm bsearch result

Upstream-Status: Pending

`known` is a const lookup table. Store `bsearch()` result in a const pointer
to avoid discarded-qualifiers errors when building with strict host toolchains.


diff --git a/libcpu/riscv_disasm.c b/libcpu/riscv_disasm.c
index 7c70bce7..f2bd2683 100644
--- a/libcpu/riscv_disasm.c
+++ b/libcpu/riscv_disasm.c
@@ -1256,7 +1256,7 @@
		  if (rd != 0)
		    op[last++] = REG (rd);
		  struct known_csrs key = { csr, NULL };
-		  struct known_csrs *found = bsearch (&key, known,
+		  const struct known_csrs *found = bsearch (&key, known,
						      sizeof (known) / sizeof (known[0]),
						      sizeof (known[0]),
						      compare_csr);
